  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6584.06 sitting directly between the max negative gamma at 6580 (-29.3B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+12.6B), dealers are caught in a volatile squeeze where they're forced to buy any dips toward 6580 and sell any rallies toward 6605, creating amplified moves in both directions. The breakout regime with -150B total GEX means dealers are structurally short gamma and will chase momentum - if we break below the 6580 wall, expect accelerated selling as dealers dump hedges into weakness. Key battleground is the 6580-6590 corridor where over -53B in negative gamma creates a feedback loop of volatility amplification.\n\nThe wall break and GEX surge events signal we're at an inflection point where any directional move will be magnified by dealer flows rather than dampened.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings between 6580 and 6605 with any break outside this range triggering momentum acceleration.",
